day\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA TODAY\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\"}, {\"begin\": 839, \"end\": 876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 839, \"end\": 876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 923, \"end\": 926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.069281776446442e-27, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 977, \"end\": 980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9802664117875688, \"rank\": 0.019810415974106526, \"text\": \"CBS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. Olympic officials revealed plans to challenge this decision.\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1060, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Given these circumstances, we are committed to pursuing an appeal to help Jordan Chiles receive the recognition she deserves,\\\" the U.S. committee said, CBS News reported.\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1233, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1137, \"end\": 1150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}, {\"begin\": 1215, \"end\": 1223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_News\", \"score\": 0.9999641504803608, \"rank\": 3.585077781158294e-05, \"text\": \"CBS News\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We remain dedicated to supporting her as an Olympic champion and will continue to work diligently to resolve this matter swiftly and fairly.\\\"\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1376, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The controversy began whenTeam USAcoach Cecile Landi filed an appeal outside the allowed one-minute window after scores were posted, seeking a 0.1 increase to Chiles' score.\", \"from\": 1378, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CAS' decision to restore the original order now positions Barbosu third, her Romanian teammate Sabrina Maneca-Voinea fourth, and Chiles fifth, ESPN stated.\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1552, \"end\": 1555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.069281776446442e-27, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 1647, \"end\": 1654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sabrina_Spellman\", \"score\": 0.9479056610480366, \"rank\": 0.054957303340060513, \"text\": \"Sabrina\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sabrina_Spellman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sabrina_Spellman\"}, {\"begin\": 1695, \"end\": 1699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\", \"score\": 0.9999999348667664, \"rank\": 6.020752157983742e-08, \"text\": \"ESPN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(RELATED: Steph Curry's Insane Heroics Seal Deal For America In Olympics)  The situation has stirred public reaction.\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1717, \"end\": 1728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steph Curry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was previously reported that RomanianPrime Minister Marcel Ciolacudeclared Tuesday that he's skipping the ParisOlympicsclosing ceremony, protesting what he views as an unfair scoring decision in women's gymnastics,accordingto Fox News.\", \"from\": 1825, \"to\": 2063, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2054, \"end\": 2062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 0.9999999760345876, \"rank\": 2.3841158155059544e-08, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PARIS, FRANCE - AUGUST 05: Jordan Chiles of Team United States competes in the Artistic Gymnastics Women's Floor Exercise Final on day ten of the Olympic Games Paris 2024 at Bercy Arena on August 05, 2024 in Paris, France.\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2065, \"end\": 2078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999995773026497, \"rank\": 4.223629595663689e-07, \"text\": \"PARIS, FRANCE\", \"types\": [\"Q4869